     <h1>Isabella Stewart Gardner Museum!<h1>
          <h3>The Isabella Stewart Gardner Museum is full of rich history! On March 18th 1990 in 81 minutes 2 men stole 13 paintings which all together were worth 500 million dollars at the Isabella Stewart Gardner Museum. To this day the paintings were never found, however, if you have any information on the location of the artwork you will get 10 million dollars! But besides the rich history the Isabella Stewart Gardner Museum still has lovely pieces of art (and 13 frames for the missing pieces of art) and a beautiful garden! We highly recommend this museum to lovers of art who are also interested in the history of the pieces of art. There is a lovely garden but this museum might not be the best for young children because there is a lack of hands on activities.
